description:
76 pages of gamma-charged action!

The Abomination is back from the dead! Bruce Banner's fate hangs in the balance as a stunning new story begins! By Mark Waid and Mark Bagley!

She-Hulk clashes with Tony Stark! A hot new series begins by Charles Soule and Javier Pulido!

Charles Xavier needs the help of Bruce Banner – which means the X-Men must face the Hulk! Classic action from Roy Thomas and Sal Buscema!

Featuring material first published in Hulk #1-2, She-Hulk #1 and X-Men #66.

76 pages of claw-popping mayhem!

Wolverine has lost his healing factor, and that's just the start of the bad news! A new mission leads to Wakanda – and a fighting-mad Black Panther! By Paul Cornell and Alan Davis!

Deadpool, Power Man and Iron Fist face the vengeance of the White Man! By Gerry Duggan and Scott Koblish!

Featuring material first published in Wolverine #7-8, Deadpool #14 and Marvel Comics Presents #10.

deck: The perfect pocket-sized art book for Lady Death fans
description: The perfect pocket-sized art book for Lady Death! That's right, this "Black Book" contains a miniature gallery of 64 cover images and sexy pin-up shots of Lady Death collected in this flip-through compact, square-bound book! Features gorgeous Lady Death art by all the Top Chaos! Artists!
Major Big Jim Willett and his company of Union soldiers have stumbled upon a bizarre crime scene. They are seeking who is responsible.

A collection of sketches, studies, and schematics, Appleseed ID is a must-have companion book for fans of the cyberpunk saga Appleseed and its legendary creator, Shirow Masamune, the manga mastermind behind such classics as Appleseed, Dominion, and Ghost in the Shell. Sit back and relax as Shirow takes you on a guided tour of one of his most beloved worlds, exploring the people, places, organizations and, of course, technology that make the universe of Appleseed the sci-fi hotspot that it is. Feel like taking a break from Shirowís examination and explanation of his creations, and of his own creative process? Then take a browse through this book's beautiful color galleries, or follow Deunan and Briareos on a high-stakes adventure with the short story "Called Game."

Shirow is well-known and critically acclaimed internationally, and is responsible for numerous classic anime/manga titles, such as Appleseed, Dominion, Ghost in the Shell, Orion, and Black Magic.

Produced in the authentic right-to-left reading format, as originally published in Japan.
name: TPB

description: The Boombox is a whimsical tale of a young , quixotic robot who embarks on a heroic quest to save and retrieve his stolen boom box.

The creators behind the legends of Spider-Man, Superman, Wonder Woman, and more were hardly overnight successes. Read the collected biographies of Stan Lee, Jack Kirby, Jerry Siegel, Joe Shuster, and William M. Marston, the creative forces behind the superheroes that started a revolution in graphic fiction storytelling.
name: TPB

volume.name: Comic Creators: Stan Lee, Jerry Siegel, Joe Shuster, Jack Kirby & William M. Marston

description: A Computer Science teacher living in Los Angeles stumbles upon a mysterious pair of pants that allows him to tap into the dark side of his personality. Hilarious and lascivious antics ensue.
name: Vol. 1

description: Salome's marriage to Ralph, a man thirty years her senior, was considered scandalous. While she lead a life of fun and leisure with Ralph, and their surprising divorce left her financially secure, it's not what she desires. When Salome looks into selling her apartment, she finds that her neighbor is Mike Angellini, a world-famous restaurateur who has always given her the cold shoulder. High society thinks Salome was a paid mistress, but she wants Mike to know the truth. Having donated all her money to charity, Salome wishes to put the past behind her, but will she find Mike's menu to be too appetizing?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Gargoyles Don't Cry

A seedy dealmaker promises to free The Gargoyle from his nightly curse. All our hero has to do is deliver a bag. Too easy? Yeah, that's what he thinks too. Find out what happens when Gargoyle By Moonlight tangles with supernatural gangs and the all-new creepy-crawly overlord of the underworld.
name: Gargoyles Don't Cry

description: An odd, perfectly timed string of events brings together two lovelorn people: Miranda Easton and Gianni Fitzgerald. In a shared country cottage, these two strangers battle their inner emotions, while seeking solace in the arms of the other. Fate has brought about this chance meeting of these two emotionally battered individuals, but was it all just so it could end with them being nothing more than star-crossed lovers?
name: Vol. 1

description: A secret society known as The Church has been preventing the birth of the second son of God for the past millennium. Their team of highly trained operatives is made up of former hitmen, wayward soldiers or anyone else looking for redemption. They will stop at nothing to track and kill the carriers of the Godchild. Convinced that they are exterminating the antichrist, they will use any means necessary while fighting a secret battle to save both the world and their souls. But sometimes, the carriers fight back... Unbeknownst to her, Maggie, has been chosen as the next carrier of the Godchild. Her life has never been fair. But, being thrown out of her home at the age of 16 for being gay has endowed her with the strength she will need in the coming months. With assassins on her trail, her will to survive and transform may not be good enough to save her. Will she live to give birth to the child of a God, or something else? From co-creator D.J. Coffman (Hero By Night).
name: Chapter One

description: The death of a denizen of the monster populace would typically get swept under the rug by human authority, but that changes when Hank Steiner: Monster Detective shows up to investigate. The monstrous private investigator gets caught up in a dangerous cover-up involving a local gang of Goblin thugs and Vampire floozies. The real threat, however, could spell doom for all monster kind.
jimbo and hurricane hit the jackpot when a case of sausages fall into their hands, but they soon are running a gauntlet of rascals, including a tribe of feral cats, ready to jump their claim!

The Hulk has seen the future...and it is murder. Beloved Hulk writer Peter David brings readers two classic dystopian tales of earth-shaking impact. Both stories find the Hulk at the end of the Earth -- and at the end of his rope! In "Future Imperfect," the Hulk is the last super power in a post-apocalyptic Earth, ruling with an iron fist as the wicked Maestro. But summoned from the past by a small band of rebels is perhaps the only being who can stand against him! And in "The End," the green-skinned titan walks alone through a wasted and barren land -- and must confront the one who is easily his ultimate nemesis!

Collects Incredible Hulk: Future Imperfect #1-2, Incredible Hulk: The End.
name: TPB

description: The inaugural issue of Jetstream is a random sampling of complete short stories that began as a university project.

Knights is comedic horror set in the dark ages. Sir Angus and Sir Dante are zealous inquisitors, who are on a holy quest to cleanse the world of evil. Vampires, demons, witches, women, heretics, elderly women, snakemen, redheads, suspicious women, all beware their blessed steel
name: The Shapeshifter & Other Short Stories

description:
AXIS tie-in! Loki faces his greatest challenge yet: Dr. Doom! But with Valeria Richards in the mix, who's the hero of this story -- and who's the villain? Loki learns that Doom has sentenced him to death for the crimes of his future self! But with the Red Skull drowning Doom, Latveria and the entire world in a wave of telepathic hate, will there even be a future left to save? And when the events of AXIS invert Loki, he begins a noble quest for truth, justice and the Asgardian way -- which pits him against the Enchantress, Lorelei...and the brutish Thor, god of evil?! Loki's inversion has another side effect, one that looks like it will stick around: the God of Lies can now only ever speak the truth. This might not go so well.

Collects Loki: Agent Of Asgard (2014) #6-11.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Loki: Agent of Asgard: I Cannot Tell A Lie

description: The collected Margarin comics, finally in english!

Earless

A mysterious book. Invisible creatures. A terrible garage band. A trip to the thrift store. All this and more await you in this, the first chapter of The Non-Seen.
name: Earless

description:
OPERATION NEMESIS: A Story of Genocide & Revenge is a graphic novel honoring the 100th anniversary of the Armenian Genocide.

Before Adolf Hitler, there was Talaat Pasha, leader of the Turkish Ottomon Empire. In 1915 Pasha ordered the mass execution of every Armenian within his nation’s borders, resulting in the death of over 1,500,000 victims.

This is the story of Soghomon Tehlirian, the Armenian survivor who killed Pasha on the streets of Berlin… and walked away from court a free man.

Note: The digital edition (4/22/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: GN

volume.name: Operation Nemesis: A Story of Genocide and Revenge

description:
The Beginning

Read the true beginning of Outlawed Justice! Uncover how the path to becoming heroes for Tony and Alex was paved way before the tragedy at the Mayor's house.
name: The Beginning

description: Introducing all-new comic creations: THE MIGHTY SAMSON (adventure), ARMORED CHAMPION (superhero adventure), STEEL SOLDIERS (sci-fi), FALCONE (comedy/adventure), THE NANIS (mystery/suspense/action), THE EXTREMIST (spy/action), SILVER GRIMOIRE (supernatural) and THE VIBRANT ONES (superhero adventure).
name: Vol. 1

description:
All Roads Lead to...

Rome, 2114.

The corrupt and cruel have made Rome a city only for the rich.

Michelangelo Tornatore, a freedom fighter better known as The Roman Nose, aims to change all that.

Hold on to your seat as he and his friends tear through the futuristic streets of Rome with trouble at their heels, fighting to bring power back to the people!
name: Book 1

description:
Worth the trouble

Scoundrel's Quest is set in a fantasy world. In which our scoundrel's "procure" certain items and/or riches for others or themselves. During which they erm... have a lot of adventures.
name: Worth the Trouble

description:
"I used to smile...

...when I thought about good things happening to other people."

When a sea urchin lurks within your brain, how can you overcome its spiky poison to live your life? Laura takes a powerful look at creativity and depression, reflection and burdens, transmitted through her art that ranges from the mundane to the fantastical.
name: GN

description: Witness the birth of America's first patriotic superhero! When FBI agent Joe Higgins dons his costume, he becomes the amazing Shield! Under the direct orders of J. Edgar Hoover, Shield will battle international spies, war machines and nature itself to keep America safe. Join us in this special presentation of The Shield's first appearances from 1940. Includes a special introduction from Robert M. Overstreet of the Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide.
name: TPB

description:
Who is the Strongest?

Danny 'The Lamb' Foreman is going to become a Pro Rugby player, even if it kills him. It most probably will.
name: Who Is the Strongest?

description: A Soulfire tale lost in time returns as a collected edition! This special Soulfire: Chaos Reign collection brings together the acclaimed 3-issue miniseries, along with the sold-out #0 issue! Adding to its appeal, the Soulfire: Chaos Reign collection also contains a brand new cover by series artist Marcus To and colorist Peter Steigerwald! In a time where power ruled over the primal landscape of the world, a hidden savagery lurks, and the only thing one can hope to do among the chaos is survive!

Collecting issues #0-5, this stunning tale introduces readers to a world full of wonder, dragons, deception, and the fall of magic! As an added bonus this contains a 7-page tale which sets the stage for the events that occur within Dying of the Light.

Collecting issues #1-3! London, 1914: The leaders of the radical women's rights movement are fugitives from the law. Their last line of defense is the secret society of "Amazons": women trained in the martial art of bartitsu and sworn to defend their leaders from arrest and assault.

After a series of daring escapes and battles with the police, the stakes rise dramatically when the Amazons are forced into a deadly game of cat and mouse against an aristocratic, utopian cult . . .

Presenting:

  • Persephone Wright, a "fallen woman" who will protect those she loves at all costs
  • "Flossie" Le Mar, a rough-diamond adventuress from New Zealand
  • Katie "Sandwina" Brumbach, a fiercely loyal Austrian wrestler and strongwoman
  • Toupie Lowther, a cunning, cross-dressing woman of means
  • Judith Lee, a proud Anglo-Chinese socialite and amateur detective
  • Kitty Marshall, a quick-witted teenager who keeps her radicalism secret from her wealthy family
  • Miss Sanderson, an enigmatic "governess" with an appetite for violence
name: GN

volume.name: The Foreworld Saga: Suffrajitsu: Mrs. Pankhurst's Amazons

description:
How much would you pay for perfection? Beauty? Immortality? Tony Stark knows, and he's ready to give it to you -- but at a terrible price! The AXIS effect has changed Tony: He's more stylish, more confident and more cunning than ever before. And he's ready to lead San Francisco into the future -- but the first step is to release Extremis upon the entire city! Daredevil isn't down with Stark's new vision of the future -- but can the Man Without Fear lead the rebellion against the Superior Iron Man? How far will Tony go to keep the secret of his success private? As Tony's actions become more questionable, who will conspire to take him down? Has his negligence bred monsters? And will those monsters destroy him? A bold new direction for the Armored Avenger begins!

Collects Superior Iron Man #1-5.
name: Volume 1

description:
Collecting the miniseries by author Samit Basu (The GameWorld Trilogy, Turbulence, Resistance) and Ashish Padlekar (Walk-In).

Some old stories never lose their bite... Something's invading the stories of our childhood, leaving death and oblivion in its wake. Now, a motley crew of animal heroes from ancient Indian fables must unite to survive. But first they must find the boy destined to save them, the chosen guardian of the Panchatantra. Thing is... he has no idea they even exist. Vishnu Sharma, would be boy-hero, is too busy playing in online tournaments to care about fighting storybook wars. But when a none-too-fictional talking lion, monkey and bull arrive at his doorstep, Vishnu must choose between protecting the tales of the Panchatantra, or silently standing by as they disappear into storybook history. With naughty boy wizards, cuddly anime-sociopaths, and a not-so-frightful King of the Jungle.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: The Tall Tales of Vishnu Sharma: Panchatantra

description:
Continued from THE THIRD: REVELATION

On the run and in possession of The Third, Devan and Anneli must outwit bounty hunters and stay alive long enough to discover its secret. But the bounty hunters are the least of their problems as a larger conspiracy emerges and others join the hunt.
name: Volume 2

description: This first issue of the ongoing comic "Tin" introduces the two main characters, Rob and A.L.I.C.E and is the setup for a grand, dangerous and exciting adventure.

In suburban Los Angeles, 8 year-old Casey Schmidt is introduced to the new next-door neighbors, specifically the pretty red-head who seems equally intrigued. Introductions are turned upside down when it's revealed little Casey is not a boy but a girl. In Tokyo, four year old Yoshiko Watanabe and her brothers are introduced to their newly adopted little sister, a baby from England that her parents seemed to have acquired under mysterious circumstances.

From the pages of DEATH OF WOLVERINE! Logan may be dead -- but what will happen to his mortal remains, encased in Adamantium? The battle for control of this valuable artifact has begun, death is on the books for a dozen heroes and villains, and Mystique is playing chess with them all! As Sinister strikes, Daken lies crippled, and death looms for Shogun's Weapon X crew. Only Wolverine's legacy -- X-23, Sabretooth, Mystique and Lady Deathstrike -- can save them all. But none of them can be trusted! Then: introducing Fantomelle, the world's most unstoppable thief, engineered to perfection! But will she be destroyed by a nightmarish monster before the Wolverines can recruit her? And surprises lay in store when the Wolverines assault Mr. Sinister's fortress! Sinister has plans for Logan's body -- but how are the Amazing X-Men involved?

Collects Wolverines (2015) #1-5.
name: Volume 1

description: The first graphic novel in the long awaited TZK series. A devastating pro-virus, planted inside human DNA in pre-history, has found its way into the wreckage of a plane crash in the Florida wilderness, only for a group of friends to discover it... and unwittingly unleash the apocalypse!
name: Volume II Book II

description:
An experimental vaccine has turned it's patients into zombies. To create a public spectacle, they are released and hunted to the point of extinction.

Z.O.R.N. must fight to stay alive, and to regain his humanity, before the secret dies with him!
Reprints issues 5-11 of Redfox

Sheeeee'ssssss baaaaaccckkkk!!!

It seems you can't keep Janey Belle down. After her first series turned thousands of fans onto our unique undead gal, we knew her story couldn't be over (She's a zombie! She can't die!!??)... But Janey's creator was ready to draw something else for a while (fairies it seems, but more on that another time). Then we started to see legions of converts to her tales in person at shows, and suddenly, WHAM-O, Dan was ready to draw more zombies!

So, we're back for volume two, and picking up right where we left off. Though, I think you'll see, Dan's got some new things in store for our favorite flesh-gobbling tramp... and I don't just mean her ever-changing fetish fashion! (or hey, take a look, there's even a new color this time!! We spared no expense for this sequel folks!)

All aboard!!
name: The Taint Train of Terror! Part 1
The Power Rangers Meet Ivan Uzi
